    <p>{`FRG allows us to interpolate smoothly between known microscopic laws and the complicated collective phenomena in macroscopic physical systems. Figuratively speaking, FRG acts as a microscope with a variable resolution. At high-resolution, we observe the microphysical laws whereas dialing to a low resolution allows us to obtain a coarse-grained picture of macroscopic collective phenomena. In this sense, it marks the amazing achievement of enabling us to cross the bridge from simple microphysics to complex macrophysics, thereby helping us understand how particular features of the former manifest as behavior in the latter.`}</p>

